Name: The Guilty
Review: Honestly one of Jake Gyllenhaal's better pieces I've seen. In between this, Nightcrawler, and other pieces, he is very emotional and captivating in his performance. I was shocked at how glued to the screen I was at at every new piece of information, and every new call. Keeps you clinged on waiting to see what's going to happen.

Name: We Have a Ghost
Review: Honestly the premise if you're looking for something on in the background or light-hearted sure not bad, but trying to watch this out of joy was difficult I stopped 3 times before I finished because oh how lost the movie felt in what it wanted to be, not scary enough to be horror, not that overly funny, and still tries to be a heartfelt family movie for a family you don't really connect with. Actors did awesome with what they were given, but the overall movie pretty mehğŸ¤·

Also Sophie Thatcher and Chloe East giving me budget Thomasin Mackenzie and Anya Taylor-Joy vibes lol

Name: Eraserhead
Review:
Surreal, and brutally honest, truly brave. To call this a movie would be a disservice. This is a proper expression of someone's art. It's not going to make sense with everyone and not everyone will get it, I'm not even sure I fully got all the layers, but the expression of self and craft of David Lynch is something to sit with in this one and ponder.

Also, adorable baby
